OL,6,FThe judge noted that Rose had already
OL,7,Fbeen to Sainsbury's earlier that day
OL,8,Fand her return trip at the time of the
OL,9,Ffire was not to purchase any items
OL,10,Fthat were "essential or vital".
OL,12,FHe told Rose: "You were not there and
OL,13,Fthe children were too young to know
OL,14,Fwhat to do. As a result of what you
OL,15,Fdid, they were all killed."
OL,17,FHe described the victims as lively and
OL,18,Fengaging children who were "deeply
OL,19,Floved" by all who had a role in their
OL,20,Fcare.
